The paper deals with the algorithmic problem of approximating the noise sensitivity of a Boolean function, which is a fundamental property of Boolean functions and is related to several other important properties such as total influence and bias. This makes it likely to belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories.
